RACE.RACE_TEXT: ZIA PARK RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Special Weight Purse 55000. FOR REGISTERED NEW MEXICO BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. (Horses which have started for $25,000 or less in their last three starts are least preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NO BULL DARWIN broke outwardly, stalked the leading pair from outside, travelled four to five wide through the turn edging nearer by the top of the stretch, bid in mid-stretch while drifting in a bit, dueled briefly then edged away. ART CURATOR dueled inside a rival but off the fence in the two to three path, put that one away but was engaged by a new foe in upper stretch, could not match strides with that one. WHISPER'S MARK switched out off the inside in the early going, was off the leaders three wide into the turn moving out five wide later on that bend, swung nine deep turning into upper stretch, was gaining but too late. CANDY TRACK settled off the pace inside saving ground through the turn, came out in mid-stretch bumping and bothering a rival nearing the sixteenth pole. CHARLIENE contested the early pace from outside three wide, weakened and switched out in mid-stretch. MI PRINCESA broke a step slowly and in a bit tight, was coaxed along two to three wide into the turn, swung out seven wide into upper stretch, was put in tight quarters between runners when lightly bumped nearing the sixteenth pole, steadied and altered out and was not persevered with thereafter. KAMMYS KASH broke a step slowly, lacked early speed, raced a bit erratic and greenly while kept well off the rail in the five path, floated nine deep leaving the turn, was never near enough to threaten. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE STRETCH RUN CANDY TRACK WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FOURTH AND PLACED SIXTH BEHIND MI PRINCESA FOR INTERFERENCE.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEAU VERO ran off pace from the leaders then dueled late on the turn taking the lead in the stretch and held to the wire. DRINKROUNDTHETRUTH ran in the middle of the pack then caused interference up the backstretch with KING BRYCE but kept hard driving down the stretch finishing up in second. UNBRIDLED OPTIMIST pressed the pace early on in the race then started dueling BEAU VERO in the middle of the turn as they came down the stretch they lost the edge on BEAU VERO close to the wire. NO GAIN N NO WILL ran in the middle of the pack on the outside then coming out of the turn they drifted inside and started making a closing bid to end up in fourth. STACKERS was bumped into a rival early, raced in the back of the pack but with a steady gain in pace made up ground as the race progressed. LET EM RIP had good speed leaving the gate then maintained their pace throughout the turn then hung mid stretch. KING BRYCE ran with good early speed then was forced into a foe and shuffled back and maintained pace after. MIST N SEVEN was bumped early, ran in the middle of the pack with a steady pace they maintained throughout the race. JEWELS AND JAZZ ran with a good early pacing then coming around the turn started to fall back but ended up fading around the quarter pole. ONEDRUNKNIGHT got off slow from the start then trailed throughout the race. THERE WAS A JOCKEYS OBJECTION FROM KING BRYCE ON DRINKROUNDTHETRUTH FOR INTERFERENCE, AFTER THE STEWARDS REVIEW THEY DETERMINED THAT DRINKROUNDTHETRUTH DID IMPEDED THE PATH OF KING BRYCE AND CAUSED A CHAIN REACTION TO OTHERS AND DISQUALIFIED THAT RUNNER TO EIGHTH.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOER NOT A FAKER had the early lead, was overtaken before the half-mile marker ceding the lead to press from inside but just off the fence, was resurgent turning into upper stretch retaking command, moved clear by mid-stretch then lasted to hold off a late run of a rallying foe. FIRST AGAIN moved up inside foes but just off the fence into the turn, moved out further coming into upper stretch three to four wide in behind the leaders, surged late but just missed. MAMA WAS A ROCKET was bumped at the start, coaxed forward between runners, made the lead outside the half racing three to four wide, was challenged late on the turn, overtaken at the top of the stretch, lacked the needed late kick. TIZ A JOURNEY was forwardly-placed pressing outside five wide just off the leaders, kept on evenly in the stretch. MOONLIGHT WARRIOR broke outwardly bumping and bothering the outer two foes, was forced out by a rival heading to the turn, fanned seven wide into upper stretch, evened out. SHAME ON CHARLOTTE was in a bit tight just after the break and raced a little awkwardly early, trailed, saved ground, passed tired foes inside. JENNY'S PENNY switched out off the inside up the backstretch, raced toward the back three wide into the turn, came out wider for the drive, had no rally. LEONAS GIRL was forced out and had some bumps at the start while being shuffled back a bit, lacked early speed racing well off the inside going in the five to six path into the turn, floated nine wide into upper stretch, was not a threat. LEAP YEAR NIGHT was forwardly-placed pressing briefly from between runners four wide, dropped back on the turn, floated out wider into upper stretch and continued fading. BETTER BELIEVE reared at the start losing the rider. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY INTO THE START IT WAS DETERMINED ALL RUNNERS RECEIVED A FAIR BEGINNING.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANCIENT LAND had the early lead inside into the first turn but was overtaken past the seven-eighths easing back content to track from in behind the leaders up the backstretch, shifted out five wide coming to the quarter pole, drifted out a bit further in upper stretch taking the lead just past the eighth pole and continuing to drift a bit, prevailed. HENRY ON THE RUN went back to the paddock to get a new rider, was floated five wide into the first turn, made a strong middle move still about five wide, took the lead near the five-sixteenths making a bid outside runners, was in command with a narrow advantage while drifting in a bit in upper stretch, overtaken in mid-stretch and outfinished but saved the place. ALL CHROME was floated six wide into the first turn, made a steady advance widest of all into the far turn, kept on in the stretch, missed second. SPINNING BLACK broke outwardly, moved forward three wide pressing into the first turn, took the lead soon after and moved clear while shifting in a bit to set the pace from just off the rail up the backstretch, was challenged by a couple outside foes on the far turn, weakened in the stretch. COMET CAUSEY was caught five wide outside runners into the first turn stalking the pace, moved forward up the backstretch to press four then three wide, bid between foes on the far turn, lacked the needed late kick. THUNDER DOME was forwardly-positioned early between foes, eased back then was taken back further early up the backstretch, switched out and was urged along about the half-mile marker, swung eight wide into upper stretch, passed tired foes. MCTHANKS angled in early on the first turn to avoid being caught extra wide, raced in behind about three deep, steadied on heels near the five-eighths, was encouraged along on the far turn racing five to six deep, ran on evenly. MCMERCELUS was forced out at the start, drifted four wide into the first turn then came back in a bit racing off the pace, was in behind about mid-pack and off the rail into the far turn, made no late bid. COLOR ME GONE had forward position four deep between runners into the first turn, steadily dropped back up the backstretch, shifted in, failed to rally.
